<subSubSection id="A5BF0DB9FFD7FF98B397B877FB31AD5C" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="ED1A5E32FFD7FF98B397B877FDB5AC18" blockId="14.[151,1437,150,861]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="DFD18220FFD7FF98B397B877FEE1AF88" bold="true" box="[199,317,367,393]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks:</emphasis>
The genus falls within 
<taxonomicName id="2AA525B1FFD7FF98B119B877FD1DAF88" authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1849" box="[585,705,367,393]" class="Malacostraca" family="Arcturidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Arcturidae</taxonomicName>
as diagnosed by 
<bibRefCitation id="893423C3FFD7FF98B0D7B877FBC2AF88" author="Poore, G. C. B." box="[903,1054,367,393]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="205 - 230" refId="ref20049" refString="Poore, G. C. B. (2001) Isopoda Valvifera: Diagnoses and relationships of the families. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 21, 205 - 230. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 20021975 - 99990118" type="journal article" year="2001">Poore (2001)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName id="2AA525B1FFD7FF98B77AB877FB13AF88" authorityName="Schultz" authorityYear="1981" box="[1066,1231,367,393]" class="Malacostraca" family="Arcturidae" genus="Spectrarcturus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DFD18220FFD7FF98B77AB877FB13AF88" box="[1066,1231,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Spectrarcturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles mostly 
<taxonomicName id="2AA525B1FFD7FF98B3C7B88BFE76AFAC" authority="Latreille, 1829" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1829" box="[151,426,403,429]" class="Malacostraca" family="Arcturidae" genus="Arcturus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DFD18220FFD7FF98B3C7B88BFF24AFAC" box="[151,248,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Arcturus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="893423C3FFD7FF98B251B88BFE76AFAC" author="Latreille, P. A." box="[257,426,403,429]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="1 - 584" refId="ref19817" refString="Latreille, P. A. (1829) Les Crustaces, les Arachnides et les Insectes, distribues en familles naturelles. In: Cuvier, G. (Ed.), Le Regne Animal distribue d'apres son organisation, pour servir de base a l'histoire naturelle des animaux et d'introduction a l'anatomie comparee. Nouvelle Edition, revue et augmentee. Deterville, Paris, pp. Xxvii + 1 - 584. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 11575" type="book chapter" year="1829">Latreille, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, another genus largely confined to the Northern Hemisphere, with which it shares a lack of flexure between the carpus and propodus of pereopods 2–4. It differs in having a short antennal flagellum rather than multiarticulate as in 
<taxonomicName id="2AA525B1FFD7FF98B2E4B8C3FDC9AFF4" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1829" box="[436,533,475,501]" class="Malacostraca" family="Arcturidae" genus="Arcturus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DFD18220FFD7FF98B2E4B8C3FDC9AFF4" box="[436,533,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Arcturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and absence of the dactylus on pereopod 1. Few species of 
<taxonomicName id="2AA525B1FFD7FF98B7E2B8C3FACFAFF4" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1829" box="[1202,1299,475,501]" class="Malacostraca" family="Arcturidae" genus="Arcturus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DFD18220FFD7FF98B7E2B8C3FACFAFF4" box="[1202,1299,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Arcturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have lateral wings on the pleotelson (
<bibRefCitation id="893423C3FFD7FF98B2FFB8E7FD80AC18" author="Kussakin, O. G." box="[431,604,511,537]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="1 - 463" refId="ref19608" refString="Kussakin, O. G. (1982) Morskye I solonovatovodnye ravnonogie rakoobrasnye (Isopoda) cholodnix I umerennix vod severnogo polushariya [Marine and brackish water like-footed crustaceans (Isopoda) of cold and temperate waters of the North- ern Hemisphere]. Podotryadi Anthuridea, Microcerberidea, Valvifera, Tyloidea. Opredeliteli po Faune SSSR, Izdavaemye Zoologicheskim Institutom Akademii Nauk SSSR, 131 (2), 1 - 463. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1982">Kussakin 1982</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ED1A5E32FFD7FF98B397BB3BFAC9ACCC" blockId="14.[151,1437,150,861]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
All species occur in the Northern hemisphere, where six species (
<taxonomicName id="2AA525B1FFD7FF98B0EEBB3BFBADAC3C" authorityName="Stransky &amp; Svavarsson &amp; Poore &amp; Kihara" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Kussakin" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[958,1137,547,573]" class="Malacostraca" family="Arcturidae" genus="Spectrarcturus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chlebovitschi">
<emphasis id="DFD18220FFD7FF98B0EEBB3BFBADAC3C" box="[958,1137,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">S. chlebovitschi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2AA525B1FFD7FF98B7D1BB3BFAD7AC3C" authorityName="Stransky &amp; Svavarsson &amp; Poore &amp; Kihara" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Gurjanova" baseAuthorityYear="1955" box="[1153,1291,547,573]" class="Malacostraca" family="Arcturidae" genus="Spectrarcturus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fabulosus">
<emphasis id="DFD18220FFD7FF98B7D1BB3BFAD7AC3C" box="[1153,1291,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">S. fabulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2AA525B1FFD7FF98B64CBB3BFA49AC3C" authorityName="Stransky &amp; Svavarsson &amp; Poore &amp; Kihara" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Kussakin" baseAuthorityYear="1982" box="[1308,1429,547,573]" class="Malacostraca" family="Arcturidae" genus="Spectrarcturus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furcatus">
<emphasis id="DFD18220FFD7FF98B64CBB3BFA49AC3C" box="[1308,1429,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">S. furcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2AA525B1FFD7FF98B3C7BB5FFEE4AC60" authorityName="Stransky &amp; Svavarsson &amp; Poore &amp; Kihara" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Richardson" baseAuthorityYear="1899" box="[151,312,583,609]" class="Malacostraca" family="Arcturidae" genus="Spectrarcturus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis id="DFD18220FFD7FF98B3C7BB5FFEE4AC60" box="[151,312,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">S. intermedius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2AA525B1FFD7FF98B217BB5FFE0AAC61" authorityName="Stransky &amp; Svavarsson &amp; Poore &amp; Kihara" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Kussakin &amp; Mezhov" baseAuthorityYear="1979" box="[327,470,583,609]" class="Malacostraca" family="Arcturidae" genus="Spectrarcturus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iturupicus">
<emphasis id="DFD18220FFD7FF98B217BB5FFE0AAC61" box="[327,470,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">S. iturupicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2AA525B1FFD7FF98B15DBB5FFD54AC60" authorityName="Stransky &amp; Svavarsson &amp; Poore &amp; Kihara" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Kussakin" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[525,648,583,609]" class="Malacostraca" family="Arcturidae" genus="Spectrarcturus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="toporoki">
<emphasis id="DFD18220FFD7FF98B15DBB5FFD54AC60" box="[525,648,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">S. toporoki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) occur in the northernmost North Pacific (Bering Sea, Kurile Islands, Aleutian Islands, Sea of Okhotsk), 
<taxonomicName id="2AA525B1FFD7FF98B17CBB73FD4BAC84" authorityName="Stransky &amp; Svavarsson &amp; Poore &amp; Kihara" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Sars" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[556,663,619,645]" class="Malacostraca" family="Arcturidae" genus="Spectrarcturus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hystrix">
<emphasis id="DFD18220FFD7FF98B17CBB73FD4BAC84" box="[556,663,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">S. hystrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the northernmost North Atlantic Ocean, and 
<taxonomicName id="2AA525B1FFD7FF98B791BB73FA95AC84" authorityName="Stransky &amp; Svavarsson &amp; Poore &amp; Kihara" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Benedict" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[1217,1353,619,645]" class="Malacostraca" family="Arcturidae" genus="Spectrarcturus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="murdochi">
<emphasis id="DFD18220FFD7FF98B791BB73FA95AC84" box="[1217,1353,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">S. murdochi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs widely in the North Pacific and in Arctic waters around 
<collectingCountry id="95B21EA2FFD7FF98B042BB97FC56ACA8" box="[786,906,655,681]" name="Greenland" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Greenland</collectingCountry>
. The latter species has not been reported in the high Arctic Ocean, between these regions. The centre of diversity is in the northernmost North Pacific.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ED1A5E32FFD7FF98B397BBCFFB31AD5C" blockId="14.[151,1437,150,861]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
The species are mostly shallow water species (several occurring as shallow as 5 or 6 meters), allowing dispersal through the shallow Bering Strait (maximum depths of around 
<quantity id="2A5DF3D7FFD7FF98B009BBE2FC4AAD14" box="[857,918,762,789]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.3" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="m" value="53.0">53 m</quantity>
). Bering Strait first opened near the end of the Miocene at 5.32 MYA (
<bibRefCitation id="893423C3FFD7FF98B2F2BA07FD7FAD38" author="Gladenkov, A. Y. &amp; Oleinik, A. E. &amp; Marincovich, L. &amp; Barinov, K. B." box="[418,675,799,825]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="321 - 328" refId="ref18811" refString="Gladenkov, A. Y., Oleinik, A. E., Marincovich, L. &amp; Barinov, K. B. (2002) A refined age for the earliest opening of Bering Strait. Palaeogeograpy, Palaeoclimatology, Palaeoecology, 183, 321 - 328. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / S 0031 - 0182 (02) 00249 - 3" type="journal article" year="2002">
Gladenkov 
<emphasis id="DFD18220FFD7FF98B176BA07FD85AD38" box="[550,601,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">et al</emphasis>
. 2002
</bibRefCitation>
), but became later closed and reopened due to land-rise and glaciations, with the last opening about 11 cal ka BP (
<bibRefCitation id="893423C3FFD7FF98B1FDBA5BFC7EAD5C" author="Jakobsson, M. &amp; Pearce, C. &amp; Cronin, T. M. &amp; Backman, J. &amp; Anderson, L. G. &amp; Barrientos, N. &amp; Bjork, G. &amp; Coxall, H. &amp; de Boer, A. &amp; Mayer, L. A. &amp; Morth, C. - M. &amp; Nilsson, J. &amp; Rattray, J. E. &amp; Stranne, C. &amp; Semiletov, I. &amp; O'Regan, M." box="[685,930,835,861]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="991 - 1005" refId="ref19078" refString="Jakobsson, M., Pearce, C., Cronin, T. M., Backman, J., Anderson, L. G., Barrientos, N., Bjork, G., Coxall, H., de Boer, A., Mayer, L. A., Morth, C. - M., Nilsson, J., Rattray, J. E., Stranne, C., Semiletov, I. &amp; O'Regan, M. (2017) Post-glacial flooding of the Bering Land Bridge dated to 11 cal ka BP based on new geophysical and sediment records. Climate of the Past, 13, 991 - 1005. https: // doi. org / 10.5194 / cp- 13 - 991 - 2017" type="journal article" year="2017">
Jakobsson 
<emphasis id="DFD18220FFD7FF98B079BA5BFC86AD5C" box="[809,858,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
) and lasting until the present.
</paragraph>
